    "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add `T.annotate_compile_flags(flags)` and `T.annotate_pass_configs(configs)` DSL functions to configure compile flags and pass configs inside function bodies\n- Store `out_idx` (from `T.empty()` + `return`) as PrimFunc attr `tilelang_out_idx` instead of monkey-patching `out_idx_override`\n- All three are stored as proper PrimFunc attrs and merged at compile time (external configs take priority)\n- Annotations can be placed before or after tensor type annotations (`A: T.Tensor[...]`)\n\n## Example\n\n```python\n@T.prim_func\ndef kernel(A):\n    A: T.Tensor[[M, K], T.float32]\n    T.annotate_pass_configs({PassConfigKey.TL_ENABLE_FAST_MATH: True})\n    T.annotate_compile_flags([\"--use_fast_math\"])\n    B = T.empty([M, K], T.float32)\n    with T.Kernel(1):\n        ...\n    return B\n```\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [x] `pytest testing/python/language/test_tilelang_language_func_attrs.py` — 9 tests covering lazy/eager modes, attr presence, conflict detection, annotation ordering\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)",
